<br>
****************************************<br>
this army started a normal space marine army in codex terms but after playtesting it and muling over with friends and other local players i decided blood angels, why? because of the usual &quot;cheese&quot; statements that came out of there mouths. so...not only did i take an army that in its own state(razorbacks and small squads) emits complaints and &quot;cheesy&quot; statements but i added blood angels to the mix just to &quot;call out&quot; the real complainers.<br>
with making an army like this i knew my sportmanship would just get hosed, but i didnt care, i dont play the game for group hugs and how the hell am i gonna control how someone feels about my army. sportmanship is the player not the army, and i think alot of players confuse this or just think of it as a way of getting back at an opponent. so, with that said, i was extremely happy i made it into the top 70 percent in sportsmanship. one of the defining and probably my favorite awards i got at minneapolis was 3rd place players choice. THAT, my friends is by far the award that means the most to me. that in itself tells me i created something that other people like and wished they had. considering the first and second place finishers Shawn Kilgore, and Brice Biele, and the numerous gt awards in appearance and such i was flattered all the more.<br>
there are....if you look closely very distinct mechanisms in my army to A) keep me from capitolizing on blood angels strengths and  capitolizing on all the heavy weapons i had. so lets take a look......i paid 15 points extra for all my razorbacks and rhinos, so in theory i alreay gave 120 points to my opponent becuase i didnt need supercharged engines. now look at what happens when i black rage..i HAVE to move my vehicles and men. so...the missle launchers cant fire..the baal gets to shoot only one weapon and to make matters worse, if i deployed a vehicle hull down, im now having to make difficult terrain tests to see if i become immobilized, which happened alot becuase of the enormous amount of terrain at the gt. so again...my opponent is getting free points when i get immobilzed becuase of black rage. ok..on to the troops...5 man squads with a heavy weapon.well, yes its cheap in points on the surface..but take a closer look. they get decimated by my death company rolls, im way out numbered if i get assaulted and gee...guess what?...2 casualties cause me to take a morale check and the opponent gets half points for the squad. so...still not convinced?...try this...i took NO veteran sergeants that get free powerfists or power weapons when they join the death company and can choose to have jumpacks. still not? ok...heres the clincher, if you noticed in the pictures of my army i have exactly 5 death company painted up, and thats exactly the number i took to the gt. my rolls for the number of guyd to go to the dc at the gt: 5,2,10,6,7,5 so anything above 5 i had to just remove a model from play...free points for the opponent. dont get me wrong, im not complaining how penalized my army is, but rather the shortsightedness of the people who join the &quot;cheese&quot; camp. this army hinges on good deployment and good tactics. oh and the luck to go first. before i get the &quot;oh but you get +1 strength and +1 int on the charge!&quot; look again to the 5 man squad and the fact that the only power weapons in the army were in the command squad. this IS not an assaulting army...it has 1,2 if the death company gets any real size, squads that can assualt with any effectiveness. this army is all about calling out all the players who truely are the bad sportsmen in this game...those that cry unfair becuase the army can either kick the hell out of theirs, costs more than theirs, doesnt fit their concept of what 40k is all about, or plain just dont like lose in any way. now...i cant obviously cover everyone that has a problem with this army, but hey...i cant win em all....and aint that what its all about?  <br>
<br>
***************************************<br>
